        <type></type>
        <definition>mspass::algorithms::deconvolution::ShapingWavelet::ShapingWavelet</definition>
        <argsstring>(const mspass::utility::Metadata &amp;md, int npts=0)</argsstring>
        <name>ShapingWavelet</name>
        <qualifiedname>mspass::algorithms::deconvolution::ShapingWavelet::ShapingWavelet</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="classmspass_1_1utility_1_1_metadata" kindref="compound">mspass::utility::Metadata</ref> &amp;</type>
          <declname>md</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>npts</declname>
          <defval>0</defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Construct using a limited set of analytic forms for the wavelet. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This constructor is used to create a ricker or gaussian shaping wavelet with parameters defined by parameters passed through the Metadata object.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>md</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Metadata object with parameters specifying the wavelet. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>npts</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>length of signal to be generated which is the same as the fft size for real valued signals. If set 0 (the default) the constructor will attempt to get npts from md using the keyword &quot;operator_nfft&quot;. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
